The Herald Conrad Mupesa Mashonaland West Bureau Journalists and editors in Mashonaland West province are undergoing a one-day workshop on investigating reporting. The workshop which is being held at a hotel in Chinhoyi, is courtesy of the Voluntary Media Council of Zimbabwe (VMCZ). <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-536261" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/WhatsApp-Image-2021-03-17-at-11.20.28-360x201.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="201" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/WhatsApp-Image-2021-03-17-at-11.20.28-360x200.jpg 360w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/WhatsApp-Image-2021-03-17-at-11.20.28.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px" /> Retired journalist and former Chronicle and Manica Post editor, Geoff Nyarota is facilitating the training workshop. Nyarota challenged reporters drawn from public and private media to be ethical and show high levels of professionalism.